  "datePublished": "2020-11-23",
  "description": "I\u0026rsquo;ve been asked about Thanksgiving a lot these past few weeks. A lot. I lost count in the upper-30s, but I think I\u0026rsquo;m just shy of 50 now. Always white people, and their questions range in respectfulness, but all came with a lot of presumptions about what my answer should cover.\nEven with that many prompts, I\u0026rsquo;ve found it really hard to give anyone an answer. And so I\u0026rsquo;m drafting this letter. I spent two days thinking about what I\u0026rsquo;d say here, but I haven\u0026rsquo;t really thought of much. I talked it over with my partner, and they had some good things to say. But me? I\u0026rsquo;m still not sure.\n",
  "name": "Thanksgiving",
